Then, writing the prior distribution as $p(\theta | x I_1) = \pi(\zeta) \pi(\eta)$, (C27) gives for the desired marginal posterior distribution
$$ 
	p(\zeta | y, z I_1) = A \pi(\zeta) \int p(y z | \zeta \eta) \pi(\eta) d \eta \tag{C29}
